RACE.RACE_TEXT: WILL ROGERS DOWNS RACE 1 5F Dirt CR: 66. Claiming Purse 10000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE NOVEMBER 9. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000 (Races Where Entered For $4,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MARIA ELENA Y. G attended the pace from outside, took the lead at the seven-sixteenths, moved clear willingly on the turn, drew off in the stretch under vigorous hand urging then geared down late. HEY ROXY set the early tempo on a narrow advantage facing outside pressure from the eventual winner, steadily weakened but fought on well enough to share the place. NAUGHTY NATALIE steadied on heels outside the three-eighths shifting first inside a rival then angling out late on the turn, came into upper stretch five wide, ran on to share the place. SUNDAY'S VISION lacked early speed, advanced mildly outside three to four wide, lacked the needed late kick. MISS TYRO was away well between runners briefly then taken back off the leading pair to track, moved out a bit entering the turn, raced about in the three path, failed to menace.

ENTRY.COMMENT: no speed, outside, 3-4w, no kick

MAGNET AND STEEL was never near enough to threaten racing inside. WEST JET settled at the rear, switched out early, went three to four wide on the turn, lacked the needed late kick. FREEDOM FLASH chased two to three wide, tired. DUE TO TIMER MALFUNCTION RACE WAS HAND-TIMED.
